621.373.826] 
  [Abstract] Nonlinear-optical properties of glasses with 
microcrystals of a semiconductor compound 
CuInS[.sup]2x[/]Se[.sub]2(1-x)[/] (belonging to the 
A[.sup]1[/]B[.sup]3[/]C[.sup]6[/][.sup]2[/] type), 
whose edge of the fundamental absorption band lies in the near 
infrared spectral region (1-1.4m), were experimentally 
examined in this paper. The relationships of energy transmission 
as a function of peak intensity of the incident ultrashort 
pulses (USP), and the kinetics of changes in absorption of the 
