in a silicate glass, with 1.06, 1.14,, 1.17, and 1.22 eV width 
of the prohibited zone were examined and the results are shown 
in a graph. The experiments demonstrated that in glasses 
containing semiconductor microcrystals 
CuInS[.sup]2x[/]Se[.sub]2(1-x)[/], the character and time 
parameters of the kinetics of the absorption changes, induced by 
picosecond light pulses, depend on the excitation level, and 
also on the photon energy of the excitation and probing pulses. 
