<F P=106> [Article by E. G. Kostsov; UDC 537.226] </F>
  [Abstract] Electrooptical effect in thin ferro-electric 
films of strontium barium niobate (SBN) Ba[.sup]x[/]Sr[.sub]1- 
x[/]Nb[.sup]2[/]O[.sub]6[/] and features of its 
application as a reversive memory medium with electro-optical 
information reading, when the state of the medium element is 
determined by the polarization direction in the ferro-electric 
material were examined. The electrophysical characteristics of 
this medium are discussed. This ferro-electric material was 
selected because in addition to other high electro-optical 
parameters it exhibits other qualities: a high melting 
temperature, small values of piezoelectric losses, time 
stability of the samples, a high value of dielectric constant, 
etc. Thin- film (In[.sup]2[/]O,[.sub]3[/] + 
SnO[.sup]2[/]) - SBN film - (In[.sub]2[/]O,[.sub]3[/] + 
SnO[.sup]2[/]), obtained by high frequency sputtering method 
on sapphire substrates were used for the studies. Based on 
comparative analysis of different contemporary methods for 
obtaining multi- component 2 - 5 m thick ferroelectric 
films, 
it can be assumed that at the present time the high frequency 
sputtering is a preferred method. Figures 5, references 39: 12 
Russian, 13 Western. 

